.SH NAME
SpeechRecognitionResult.item \- SpeechRecognitionResult: item() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]item\f[B]\f[R] getter of the
\f[CR]SpeechRecognitionResult\f[R] interface is a standard getter that
allows \f[CR]SpeechRecognitionAlternative\f[R] objects within the result
to be accessed via array syntax.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
item(index)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]index\f[R]
Index of the item to retrieve.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]SpeechRecognitionAlternative\f[R] object.
.SH EXAMPLES
This code is excerpted from our \c
.UR https://github.com/mdn/dom-examples/blob/main/web-speech-api/speech-color-changer/script.js
Speech color changer
.UE \c
\ example.
.IP
.EX
recognition.onresult = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]const\f[R] color = event.results[0][0].transcript;
  diagnostic.textContent = \(gaResult received: ${color}.\(ga;
  bg.style.backgroundColor = color;
};
